{"questionId":"9070929","questionHtml":"<p>What is the relationship between acid and base dissociation constants in a conjugate&nbsp;acid–base pair?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">w</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">w</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">w</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>K</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>K</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">w</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070929","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.26","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"What is the relationship between acid and base dissociation constants in a conjugate acid–base pair? A. Ka×Kb=Kw B. KaKb=Kw C. pKa×pKb=pKw D. pKapKb=pKw","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"26","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry","5.1 Measuring energy changes","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}